G we currently use EEGLAB scripts in Matlab.", "standards_lifecycle_stages": ["From data processing — convert to standards after acquisition for processing, analysis, and publication"], "standards_usage_description": "We format the EEG data to BIDS after collection and keep as such for remainder of analyses.", "metadata_gaps": "N/A", "neural_formats_other": "None of above. Our data is collected in xdf and converted to EEGLAB fdt format.", "behavioral_data_formats": ["CSV", "Excel", "Matlab", "mpeg"], "behavioral_formats_other": "We use default formats that the data are acquired in.", "ontologies_used": ["Other"], "ontologies_other": "We would like to implement HED but have not had the opportunity to do so.", "ontologies_usage": "To describe or annotate neural data, To describe or annotate behavior", "data_management_systems": ["Shared data storage"], "primary_storage": "Institutional cluster", "data_sync_methods": ["Timestamping", "Trigger Signals", "Lab Streaming Layer (LSL)", "Hardware Synchronization (TTL)"], "neural_feature_detection": ["Statistical methods", "AI-based methods", "Domain-specific commercial", "Domain-specific open source (MNE-Python, Open Ephys)"], "behavioral_feature_detection": ["Statistical methods", "Eye-tracking methods", "Computer vision (pose estimation)", "Domain-specific commercial (Tobii Pro)"], "behavioral_feature_detection_other": "We will be developing these so this will change.", "feature_detection_software": ["MMPose", "Python", "Matlab", "PupilLabs"], "analysis_languages": ["MATLAB", "Python", "R", "Specialized neuroscience open source (EEGLAB, SPM, FreeSurfer, MNE-Python)", "Custom-built tools"], "use_analysis_method": ["Classical statistical methods", "Computational models (Markov chains)", "Time series analysis", "Unsupervised ML", "Supervised ML", "Deep learning"], "use_analysis_types": ["Statistical analysis", "Signal processing (Fourier, wavelet)", "Dimensionality reduction (PCA, tSNE, UMAP)", "Dynamical systems modeling", "